"It is true that we live in a strange world, but the recurrence of some security incidents borders on the incredible. Naturally, employees who are fired from their jobs tend to be unhappy. But a recent survey of 300 Australian IT administrators found that a whopping majority would go so far as to steal company data if they were fired. 1 According to the survey, 88% of IT administrators said openly that they would take company secrets with them on departure."
